        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 25 at 7:52PM EDT until June 25 at 8:45PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>SVRGSP

The National Weather Service in Greenville-Spartanburg has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northwestern Anderson County in Upstate South Carolina...

* Until 845 PM EDT.

* At 752 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Clemson, or
near Pendleton, moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines.

* Locations impacted include...
Pendleton, Sandy Springs, and Lake Hartwell.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Please report damaging winds, hail, or flooding to the National
Weather Service by calling toll free, 1, 800, 2 6 7, 8 1 0 1, or by
posting on our Facebook page, or Tweet it using hashtag nwsgsp. Your
message should describe the event and the specific location where it
occurred.</instruction>
